////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

        Where in Wikipedia is Carmen Sandiego
        (or Wiki Sandiego for short)

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

This is the repository for our ``Where in Wiki is Carmen Sandiego''
videogame for 6.073J Project 3 - Spring 2012.

Authors:
 * Jordan Moldow <jmoldow@mit.edu>
 * Steven Valdez <dvorak42@mit.edu>
 * Dexter Cogswell <dexter_c@mit.edu>
 * Zandra Vinegar <ch3cooh@mit.edu>

Attributions:
 * Data and images from Wikipedia (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Copyrights).
 * Theme and title are based on the game ``Where in the World Is Carmen Sandiego?''

Project home page: <github.com/jmoldow/Wiki-Sandiego>
Git repository: <github.com/jmoldow/Wiki-Sandiego.git>

To run:
$ python Main.py (for the GUI version; not yet complete)
$ python Game.py (for the text-based version)

Instructions:
You are David A. Honig, an investigator in the International Art Crime Unit of
the UN. In an unprecedented event, your unit has received 11 (22/2) messages from
Cujo Sanfran, a famous Art Thief, clueing the locations where he will be pulling
off a major heist in the coming days. It is up to you to stop him, before he steals
the masterpieces from around the world.

Instructions for the GUI and the text-based versions are different. Both sets of instructions
are available within the respective version.

Dependencies:
 * Python 2.7 <http://python.org/download/releases/2.7.2/>
 * SIP 4.13 <http://www.riverbankcomputing.co.uk/software/sip/download>
 * PyQt4 <http://www.riverbankcomputing.co.uk/software/pyqt/download>
 * Python Imaging Library (PIL) <http://www.pythonware.com/products/pil/>

This code is free and open source. Anyone can view, download, and
modify the code, but please let us know and attribute us.

Known bugs:
 * Game hangs if there is no internet connections.
 * Format of some text clippings in incorrect.
 * Database will sometimes be corrupted if not properly closed, delete the file wikicache and restart to resolve.
 * The GUI version of the game is not yet complete.
